# Power BI Data Visualization

This section highlights the Power BI data visualizations I developed for my master’s final project with Pontia.  
The goal was to design a fleet of 200 used vehicles for Europcar, supported by a €3,000,000 investment.  
The fleet had to follow a specific composition: **40% vans, 30% compact cars, and 30% sedans**.

The analysis included market benchmarking, pricing variability, vehicle performance indicators, and strategic recommendations to maximize fleet value and operational efficiency.

To build the final fleet, I filtered the dataset to include vehicles from **2018 onwards**, with the **lowest possible mileage**, and ranked them based on their **Total Cost Opportunity (TCO)**.  
This approach allowed me to identify the most cost‑efficient options and shape a balanced, data‑driven fleet composition.

